 accretion shocks at the centrifugal\nbarrier at the inner envelope. Since the molecular composition is dominated by\nthat of the accretion shocks and the radiatively heated hot inner region is\nvery compact, we propose this source to be a precursor to a classical,\nradiatively heated hot core.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 13 Oct 2019 21:05:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-27"}
